The program will run, but it will compare each adjacent pair and if they are equal, it will flip one of them to the opposite (if it was '0', flip to '1', if it was '1', flip to '0')? But what if we have a digit like '2'? The program does:

                    if (a.charAt(i) == a.charAt(i-1)) {
                        if (a.charAt(i) == '1') a.setCharAt(i, '0');
                        else a.setCharAt(i, '1');
                    } For a digit that is not '0' or '1', it will be in the else branch? So if we have two adjacent '2's, it will flip the second to '1'. Then the program continues.
